Following our successful  campaign, our  campaign is set to unlock the Terran Shield stretch goals. 

Terran Shield is a tactical underwater and above water turn-based game where you must defend the Earth against an unexpected alien invasion.

 
Continuing in the line of X-Com and Jagged Alliance series, Terran Shield proposes new gameplay features and a rich and detailed graphic style developed using the powerful Unreal Engine 4. Furthermore, a complex AI that learns and adapts to the player's style will challenge them to play at their best, crippling their efforts to save humanity from the menace of the infamous alien rulers "The Council of The Six"!
Some of the important features that Terran Shield brings to the table:

 A Time Units based central mechanic to sustain a multitude of gameplay actions that can be executed in any order, for a rich and complex gameplay;
 The Six Headed Hydra AI, which can gather resources from the ocean bed, expand, attack player's bases, research new tech, manufacture weapons and breed minions. Also, on higher difficulty levels, it analyzes the player’s game style and reacts to it, tricking him and exploiting his weaknesses;
 A reaction fire system (old X-Com games style) combined with the interrupt system (Jagged Alliance style), that make for a dynamic combat gameplay on the adversary turn;
 A complex Inventory menu that allows the player to pick up items, dead or stunned aliens, weapons and ammo from the floor, change weapons, change weapon's ammo etc.
 Top view base management with building modules: in case of an alien base attack, the module arrangement is crucial because if the aliens reach critical areas they can steal info or even destroy the human base; 
 Underwater and land environment generated random maps, each with their unique characteristics and gameplay style;
 The upgradable transport and battle vehicle The Squid, which can be specialized through a unique research tree at player's liking;  
 The Aquanaut and Soldiers abilities that will improve after every mission, in direct relationship with their usage; also, unique perks that specialize the unit and make it more powerful; these can be unlocked for every human unit (scientists, too); 
 Fully destructible environment and assets powered by Niagara VFX toolset;
 Full 3D graphics with high definition textures and dynamic lighting.

 

Get into the battle and fight the menacing alien threat in the luxuriant Borneo jungle. Help the Terran Shield forces find The Lost Shrine of UM hidden alien base and reduce their influence on this part of the globe.
 Here is the playthrough of our alpha demo on Superhuman difficulty level, with live commentary and explanations. We wanted it to be a loss-free mission, but this time the aliens got Melnikoff with their terrific sonic gun.

Terran Shield playthrough on Superhuman (Alpha demo )The aliens will take no prisoners and will fight to the last one. They are faster, with more Time Units, more Stamina and they have a 320 degree arch vision due to their laterally placed eyes. They see better in this jungle environment than us and it is likely they will spot us well before we spot them.In addition, they are equipped with the powerful Sonic Gun that is extremely precise at any range and has a tremendous destructive power. Also watch out for the mighty alien superblaster grenade, with a smaller explosive range than ours, but with more firepower and longer throw range.Last but not least: do not hastily engage on higher difficulty levels from the beginning. Without a proper expertise and experience on the tactical battlefield, you will find the combat frustrating and impossible to win.Terran Shield long trailer The most important part of Terran Shield is its strategy core component. We are striving to provide the best in the game’s other areas (graphics, sound, effects and animation), but strategy and tactics shall remain our main focus. Time UnitsThe other core goal of our philosophy is to provide the player with the freedom to express themselves within the game: the freedom to play according to their own unique style and not get penalized by the game as a result of that. One of the main features a TBS can employ to achieve this are the Time Units.The player is aided to better manage the soldier time units by the moving area graphic representation. Inside the blue area he can move and shoot, in the green area he can move and use the item in the other hand (throw a grenade, in this case) and in the red area he can only move and change stance to get better cover during the alien turn. Damage typesAnother feature that adds more depth to the strategy and tactical areas are the damage types. There are seven types of damage for the tactical combat (Battlescape) and three types of damage (kinetic/explosive, electric, sonic) for the Geoscape battles. StancesAnother feature that takes benefit from the time units game mechanics are the stances that the soldier can have during combat. All the stances have their benefits and drawbacks. For the Air Force soldiers, the crouch and prone stances improve the aim, decreasing the chance to be hit by the aliens at the same time, but they lower the movement speed of the unit making the soldier vulnerable to enemy reaction fire.The aim of the soldier is enhanced by 7% if going into crouch stance. That change of stance uses 7 time units, but gives the soldier just enough accuracy to hit the target.The aquanauts have their stances, too: normal swim, fast swim mode and the additional shooting with medium and great support. The last two are available when the aquanaut finds something solid to grip himself onto, in order to avoid being snaked by underwater currents and miss the shoot.Geoscape and base buildingThe Geoscape is the game level where the player can construct bases, intercept hostile alien crafts, launch missions, harass alien harvesting sites and bases. It will have all the old features of the ‘90s old and loved TBS games, plus some of the new features that we have in mind for our game.The Squid detecting an alien base and targeting an alien medium fighter.Building the environment and the destructible assetsThe environment possesses resistances to certain damage, as well as vulnerabilities. The player will need to take this into account when attacking or hiding behind environment objects. The environment shall be fully destructible, but certain objects like rocks can be destroyed only with heavy artillery fire or explosives.Our current tactical map terrain is a fixed layer over which the map generator lays several types of destructible assets, foliage and fauna. Having various heights on the terrain makes the random module placement very difficult to design because the edges of the modules won’t match perfectly. For the creation of a real generated terrain from modules we need additional financial resources. Until then, the current setup can make several different maps for the same landscape map, because the assets that lay over it are very diverse. For instance, on the same structure map, we can have in the same place rocks, or a building, or a forest.More about the game can be found here.The AIHaving Razvan Florian, one of the lead scientists on neural networks in our team will also aid us in this difficult endeavour. Because an AI of the complexity we need typically runs on very powerful servers, we must pack it and make it work on a usual PC, which is not an easy task.More about the AI can be found here. The story begins around the year 2035, with a rich treasure hunter named Rick Stenk and his wife Tina, who are searching for a lost artifact called “The Gift of Poseidon”. After months of no tangible results and with the aid of the psychic medium Ana Velkova, they finally manage to find the location of the precious artifact in a submerged cave near Crete.After the discovery of the Poseidon Cave, Rick receives a phone call from his brother Eugene about a strange underwater footage in the Black Sea. On it, some unusual creatures resembling frogs can be observed, clearly intelligent, working around some underwater optic cables (the cables were ours, obviously). As nobody has a better diving team, Rick is asked to help the ongoing on-site investigation, as soon as possible.More about the story can be found here. The aliens appear to be perfectly adapted to both land and water environment, which leads us to believe that their strategy is to first invade the marine depths so that later they can surface and conquer the landmasses.Ka-Um-LaUsually, the first alien encountered by Terran Shield forces in the game, named The Frogman by the aquanauts due to its appearance, the Ka-Um-La is anatomically closely related to lizards. Well adapted to an underwater environment, it uses its strong tail to swim fast and to suddenly change direction.Its large eyes enable it to see very well in limited lighting conditions and the electro-sensors provide the ability to orientate in muddy waters. On its toes the Ka-Um-La has gecko-like pads, which can be used to climb vertical walls, thus making it a formidable foe in urban areas.Jellyfish SentryThis strange creature, named the Jellyfish Sentry by the aquanauts, is a gelatinous invertebrate that has received several unknown device implants at the hand of its alien overlords.Due to its bioluminescent bacteria pouch, which can be used as a beacon, we can assume that this creature is used as a scout, uncovering the terrain and dangers that lie ahead of the alien assault units. Being a transparent creature makes it very difficult to detect in an underwater environment. The weak electrical signals it generates make it nearly invisible to the aquanauts' sensors and therefore extra effort is required to locate this perfect alien spy.Ud'GleeRipper, killer, monster.The incarnation of all the horrors lurking and hiding in the dark depths of the oceans.The large eyes and the small fluorescent lure on its forehead are indicative of a creature that is very well adapted to the dark ocean depths. It comes as no surprise that the 6 alien rulers have assigned the sonic gun to this monster, given that its vision and perception area in an aquatic environment are unparalleled. If the aliens have more specimens of this living horror in their army, then it seems that we have already lost control over the Earth’s oceans! The only way for us to regain it and have a chance to stop the alien invasion is to capture and research one of those sonic guns, the weapon this monster handles with ease. But that is easier said than done…More about the aliens can be found here.Alien weaponsDesigning the alien weapons was not an easy task. They must be designed and manufactured underwater by the alien scientists, so we had to invent a totally new manufacturing process. Also, they have to work in the air as well as underwater and they should be produced in large numbers in a short time.The Gel GunThe gel gun is designed to isolate the enemies by forcing them to avoid the areas covered in the weapon`s gel and thus forcing them to reveal their position.The weapon can also be used to capture enemies that have had the misfortune of becoming trapped in the gel. The cartridge launched by the gel gun is propelled only a relatively short distance by means of a chemical reaction in the weapon. Once the cartridge slows down, it opens up and releases a powder which, when in contact with the surrounding water transforms into a sticky gel, forming a compact, irregular mass of approximately 6 meters in diameter. Any creature that becomes trapped in the gel will find it very difficult to become unstuck, as the gel acts like a spider web.Sonic GunUnsurprisingly, the sonic gun is the main assault weapon used by the alien forces. The technology behind this artifact is incredible. Human researchers have admitted that even though they have a partial understanding of how the weapon works, they have no theory that can explain the existence of an energy pulse that can maintain the amplified sonic waves and only release them when coming into contact with a solid surface. The nature of the type of energy capable of moving at the speed of sound, while encapsulating the sound waves produced by the weapon, is entirely unknown to humans.  The SquidDuring the whole game, the main and most powerful Terran Shield ship and transport will be the Squid. The Gods’ gift for humanity is no ordinary ship. It can evolve in time and as the players progress in the game, its super-powerful batteries are charging to their full potential unlocking new offensive and defensive abilities.The Squid can be upgraded from its initial hiding place, the Poseidon Cave, where the scientists can find hints on how to unlock its powers. The Squid research branch will be very important in late game where the ship will have to compete with the enormous dreadnoughts of the aliens, with big shields and big guns.More about the weapons can be found here. Terran Shield AquabaseThe aquabases are constructed in underwater caves or, more frequently, directly on the bottom of the ocean floor.  On this particular base iteration, maybe it wasn’t such a good idea to put the war module near the alien containment module. Should one of them escape, it could break havoc on our aquabase.They are made from a few types of base modules and can host only 2 or 3 aquanaut teams. They can have alien containment modules, sub pens, sonars, living facilities, but no manufacturing of research facility. The main reason for that is that the underwater bases are filled with water, thus restricting those kinds of facilities.The AquanautThe aquanauts have had gills implanted and their lungs have been modified with a special film that can collect the oxygen from the water and deliver it to the alveoli. In addition, their eyes were modified with a supplementary reflective area in their back, so that they can see 3 times better in low light environments than a normal human.More about the Aquanaut and his equipment.  The Air Force soldiers and tactical battlesWith his initial light armour and equipped with kinetic and electric weapons, the Terran Shield Air Force usual soldier can seem an easy target for alien forces that do so well in dense forests and humid environments. But this is a mistake, for all Terran Shield Air Force soldiers are experienced and well-trained professionals from all around the world, are resilient and have a lot of combat experience.The good thing about the electric gun is that it can function under- and above water.Another factor in favour of the Air Force is that the troop transport hovercraft can bring to the battle line up to 30 fully equipped soldiers, plus additional battle robots, drones and also small artillery pieces. In fact, they have enough firepower to destroy all the hunting aliens on the tactical map. Tall and slim, the It-Um-La can sneak behind enemy lines and use a melee weapon or can launch an unexpected mortar barrage on enemy positions. Some of the melee aliens that the Terran Shield forces will encounter. Well... nobody wants to get near those.​ The splitting of the Jellyfish Sentry.​ The modified Sonic Gun below is the favourite weapon of this monster. We wonder what is its favourite food...​ The Shark attack drone helicopter. Very fast, small target for the enemy, cheap and with decent firepower. Terran Shield medivac is the fastest troops transport vehicle for small forces. It can deploy troops in difficult terrain and offer high medical assistance and recovery. "The Defender" Hovercraft "The Defender" Hovercraft - exterior​ Vehicles and soldiers placement inside "The Defender" Hovercraft​ Air Force vehicles and drones.​ The first concept for the Terran Shield Air Force soldier with advanced combat armor made with alien technology. Terran Shield land base placed at the sea shore, with underwater heavy defenses and several heavy armored docks.  Not only humans are looking for lost treasures.      We are a fresh Romanian indie game company that enjoys making special games to challenge the players while giving them a polished game-play and great replayability.At the same time, we want to remain in touch with the game community, talk to our fans about our games and adjust them if necessary. Game development schedule Risks and challengesAs with every game project, there is a risk that the end product will not be delivered as promised, or that the project will be cancelled. For strategy games in particular, the main risk is that the final game is unbalanced, as it happened before to other TBS games. In order to avoid this scenario for Terran Shield, we have established the balance between the strategy and tactical components of the game as our number one priority. Even if we run short of funds, we won’t deliver the final product until it is well-balanced and fun to play. We would rather have fewer environments and assets than provide an unfinished strategy game.

Short SummaryOur vision of a game we want to create.This game allows a player to plunge into the colorful and mysterious underwater world of microorganisms. Your character is a microbe that fights for food and survives in the unfriendly world of the same greedy and even aggressively minded microbes. "Eat or be eaten" - this is the main principle which rules everything and everyone here.
One of the main features of this world is the colorful diversity of its inhabitants. Thanks to the extremely flexible editor of the character it is possible to change the body shape, color, and texture.   
The microbe has the basic shape and the parts that have passive and active effects, which add greatly to the underwater battles variety and action. The world is filled with living organisms that are guided by artificial intelligence. Be ready to have a large number of obstacles on your way: the food is hard to hunt down and the predatory bosses do not give any opportunity to relax even for the strongest players.
